Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL post handler (10011)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL post: lowers an array literal [a, b, c] to an
alloca for the array plus a sequence of element stores. Element
values are already on the result stack in source order (reversed
by the LIFO pop pattern).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read element_count at HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL offset 16.
2. Read element_type at offset 24, array_type at offset 32.
3. Allocate the array on the stack (count = element_count,
   element_type = element_type, alignment = 8).
4. For i from element_count - 1 down to 0:
   - Pop element value from stack (LIFO so last element popped first).
   - Emit MIR_STORE at array_alloca + (i * 8) = element_value.
5. Push the array_alloca pointer as the array's MIR value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
N + 1 instruction emissions per array literal (1 alloca + N
stores). Constant arrays optimised in later passes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Zero-element arrays produce a minimal alloca; defensive against
empty literals.
@End Security_Scope

