Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_RECORD_LITERAL post handler (10013)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_RECORD_LITERAL post: lowers a record literal { field1: a,
field2: b } to an alloca plus per-field stores. The HIR node
carries a list of field-symbol pointers (each providing field
offset) which we read to determine the store address for each
value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read field_count at HIR_RECORD_LITERAL offset 16.
2. Read record_type at offset 24.
3. Read fields_list at offset 8 (List of field-info structs
   containing offset at field-info offset 8).
4. Allocate the record on the stack.
5. Pop each field value (reverse order) and store at the field's
   declared offset (8 * i for the foundation layout; real offsets
   come from the field-info struct once it lands in P2-E).
6. Push the alloca pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
N + 1 instruction emissions per record literal.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Field offset overflow is bounded by field_count * 8 < 64 KB for
realistic records.
@End Security_Scope

