Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION post handler (10014)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION post: lowers a lambda to a function-pointer
MIR value plus an optional captures record. The lambda body has
already been lowered (or rather, will be lowered as a separate
MIR function by the driver — for v0.0.8.5 the lambda body is
treated as an inline expression whose result is pushed). The
post handler emits a function-pointer constant referencing the
generated MIR sub-function and constructs a closure record if
there are captured variables.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read parameter_count at HIR_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION offset 16.
2. Read body MIR-id at offset 24 (the lambda's lowered MIR
   function id, allocated by the driver's lambda walker).
3. Read capture_count at offset 32 and captures_list at offset 40.
4. Read closure_type at offset 48.
5. Allocate a closure record alloca with one slot for the function
   pointer plus capture_count slots.
6. Store the body MIR id at offset 0.
7. For each captured variable, look up its MIR value and store it
   into the closure record at offset (i + 1) * 8.
8. Push the closure_alloca pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Capture_count + 2 instruction emissions per lambda. Cold compared
to expression leaves.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
A null body MIR id triggers a lowering error - the driver should
have populated this slot before traversal reached the lambda.
@End Security_Scope

