Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_CAST_EXPRESSION post handler (10015)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_CAST_EXPRESSION post: lowers an explicit type cast to a MIR
cast op. The child expression's MIR value is on the stack; we
read the source_type and target_type from the HIR node and emit
a unary cast instruction whose specific opcode is selected by the
cast direction (int->int, int->float, ptr->ptr, narrow, widen).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Pop source value.
2. Read source_type at HIR_CAST_EXPRESSION offset 16 and
   target_type at offset 24.
3. Read cast_kind at offset 32 (0=implicit, 1=explicit, 2=unsafe).
4. Select MIR cast opcode: MIR_BITCAST (20020) for unsafe/explicit
   pointer casts, MIR_TRUNC (20021) for narrowing, MIR_EXTEND
   (20022) for widening. The foundation pipeline uses a single
   MIR_BITCAST since LIR resolves the actual machine cast based on
   source/target types.
5. Allocate result value and emit a MIR_UNARY with the cast opcode.
6. Push result.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Single emit per cast.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Null source value is a lowering error. The HIR layer has already
validated cast safety per cast_kind; the lowering layer trusts
the input.
@End Security_Scope

