        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_value be proc lowering_pop_result from LCtx with ctx
    If source_value is equal to 0:
        proc lowering_set_error from LCtx with ctx, 35, hir_node_ptr
        Return 0
    End If

    Let target_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 24

    Let result_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
    Note: MIR_CAST (20400) — the canonical cast opcode handled by
    Note: lir_builder lower_type_conversion. The former literal 20020 was
    Note: outside every opcode band and no consumer dispatched on it
    Note: (reconciled 2026-06-10 under task #432 OD-1 contract sweep).
    Let cast_inst be proc create_mir_unary_op from MIRNodes with 20400, result_value, source_value, target_type
    If cast_inst is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, cast_inst
    End If

    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, result_value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_TYPE_ASCRIPTION post handler (10016)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_TYPE_ASCRIPTION post: a type ascription (expr: Type) is a
compile-time annotation that informs the type checker without
producing any runtime instruction. The wrapped expression's MIR
value passes through unchanged.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
No-op. The child's MIR value is already on the result stack; the
parent consumes it normally.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_type_ascription_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_FUNCTION_POINTER post handler (10017)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_FUNCTION_POINTER post: lowers a function-pointer expression
($function_name) to a MIR_CONST whose constant_value is the
resolved function's MIR id. The function id is recorded in the
HIR node at offset 16 (resolved_function symbol id) when HIR
construction resolves the name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read function_name at HIR_FUNCTION_POINTER offset 8 and
   resolved_function id at offset 16.
2. Read function_type at offset 24.
3. Allocate a result value and emit MIR_CONST(resolved_function,
   function_type, is_string=0).
4. Push result.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Single emit per function-pointer creation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
A zero resolved_function id is a lowering error (HIR resolver
should have populated this).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_function_pointer_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let builder_ctx be proc lowering_get_builder_ctx from LCtx with ctx
    If builder_ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let resolved_function be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 16
    Let function_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 24

    If resolved_function is equal to 0:
        proc lowering_set_error from LCtx with ctx, 36, hir_node_ptr
        Return 0
    End If

    Let result_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
    Let const_inst be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with result_value, resolved_function, function_type, 0, 0
    If const_inst is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, const_inst
    End If

    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, result_value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_INDIRECT_CALL pre + post handlers (10018)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_INDIRECT_CALL pre: records the argument count target into the
pending_lvalue slot so the post handler can pop exactly that many
argument values from the result stack.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read arg_count at HIR_INDIRECT_CALL offset 16 and stash via
lowering_set_pending_lvalue.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Single int64 read and write.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Defensive: arg_count of 0 is a valid no-args indirect call.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_indirect_call_pre" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 16
    proc lowering_set_pending_lvalue from LCtx with ctx, arg_count
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
HIR_INDIRECT_CALL post: consumes the function-value and N argument
values from the result stack and emits a MIR_CALL with is_indirect
= 1. The function value (a closure record or raw function pointer)
becomes the callee operand instead of a symbol-resolved name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Recover arg_count via lowering_take_pending_lvalue.
2. Pop N argument values into a List in source order.
3. Pop the function value (child_index 0, pushed first).
4. Read return_type at HIR_INDIRECT_CALL offset 24.
5. Allocate result value and emit MIR_CALL(result, function_value,
   args, arg_count, return_type, is_indirect=1, is_tail=0).
6. Push result.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Hot path for higher-order function use. Same cost as a direct call
plus the function-value computation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Null function value is a lowering error.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_indirect_call_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let builder_ctx be proc lowering_get_builder_ctx from LCtx with ctx
    If builder_ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let arg_count be proc lowering_take_pending_lvalue from LCtx with ctx
    Let return_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 24

    Let mir_args be proc create from List
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than arg_count:
        Let arg_value be proc lowering_pop_result from LCtx with ctx
        proc insert from List with mir_args, 0, arg_value
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let function_value be proc lowering_pop_result from LCtx with ctx
    If function_value is equal to 0:
        proc lowering_set_error from LCtx with ctx, 37, hir_node_ptr
        Return 0
    End If

    Let result_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
    Let call_inst be proc create_mir_call from MIRNodes with result_value, function_value, mir_args, arg_count, return_type, 1, 0
    If call_inst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, call_inst
    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, result_value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: Expression Handler Registration
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
Installs every expression-node handler in the lowering dispatch
table. Called once at the start of a lowering pass by the driver in
definition_lowering.runa. Handlers that don't need pre/child hooks
pass 0 for those slots so the trampoline short-circuits.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Sequence of lowering_register_handler calls, one per HIR
expression node type that has a dedicated handler. The function-
pointer addresses are taken implicitly by the canonical proc-
reference syntax: in this v0.0.8.5 stage1 compiler, naming a proc
in a call position yields its address when the caller's signature
expects an Integer (function-pointer type).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Cold path, called once per lowering pass. Six handler registrations.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Validates table non-null. Caller controls handler addresses.
@End Security_Scope

